Some taxi associations in Gauteng have announced they will increase fares by more than a 150%. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some taxi associations in Gauteng have announced they will increase fares by more than a 150-percent. The taxi industry says it's been severely affected by the coronavirus pandemic. They say COVID-19 regulations which force them to reduce the number of passengers has left them with no choice. Level 3: What now for public transport? The industry will be meeting on Thursday to discuss the way forward. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.